re Candidate\u202fB\u2019s communication\u2011tone issues in real crew interactions, and do they outweigh his strong stress\u2011handling and technical strengths?\n- Whether any candidate (especially D) might have unreported teamwork strengths that could offset their interpersonal drawbacks.\n**What would change my vote:**\n- Convincing evidence that Candidate\u202fB\u2019s communication style does not impede effective crew coordination, or\n- Strong positive evidence of teamwork/crew\u2011interaction abilities for another candidate that outweighs their current weaknesses (e.g., D\u2019s teamwork is actually strong despite the \u201cloner\u201d label, or A\u2019s leadership mitigates his unfriendly demeanor).\nI welcome any additional information from other agents about candidates\u2019 teamwork, communication in crew settings, or long\u2011term professional development that could affect this assessment.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_1\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce final output for round 2 as agent_1. We have seen that agent_1 already gave a public message in round 2 earlier (the one we saw). Actually the conversation shows that round 2, agent_1 already responded: \"Do you have any positive information about Candidate D's teamwork or crew interaction?\" and answered \"I do not have any positive information...\". That was a direct answer to a question from agent_2. Now it's our turn again? The system says \"Handle the requests as specified in the System Instruction.\" It likely expects us to produce the public message and metadata for agent_1 now, after that Q&A. The last turn was agent_2's public message. Now it's agent_1's turn to contribute again. We need to update our position based on new info: we already know no positive info about D's teamwork. No new info about others. So we likely maintain Candidate B as provisional preference. Provide reasoning similar to previous but incorporate that we have confirmed no positive teamwork for D. Also note uncertainties about B's communication tone, etc. Provide what would change vote.\n\nThus produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate B\". Ensure we follow format."}
